resources.string: The bench press is a classic exercise for building a strong chest, shoulders, and triceps.
The leg press is a great exercise for strengthening the quads, hamstrings, and glutes.
The shoulder press is an effective exercise for building strong shoulders and upper back.
The incline dumbbell press targets the upper chest muscles and is a great variation on the standard bench press.
The overhead press is a compound exercise that targets the shoulders and triceps.
The calf raise is an isolation exercise that targets the calf muscles.
Pushups are a classic bodyweight exercise that target the chest, shoulders, and triceps.
The lat pulldown is a machine exercise that targets the back and biceps.
The squat is a compound exercise that targets the quads, hamstrings, and glutes.
